On Wed, Aug 06, 2003 at 04:19:32PM -0400, Scott Soehlig wrote:
> I have spots of surface rust that I can sand down to bare metal...when I do
> that some of it stays in the pitted areas and I cannot sand it out...if I
> cover those areas with por15 will that be sufficient? Or does it really need
> to removed completely? I am sanding with 100 grit paper...what else should I
> use to get the rest of it out of the pitted areas? I am going to try some
> marine clean tonight....

I can't remember what Por-15 says about aplying on rust, but I really
don't think it's a great idea. A wire brush will really get a lot of
rust out of pitted areas. I have a wire wheel on my angle grinder I
use to clean out stuff like that and it works great.

